The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Lloyd Match Referee

Mumbai: Clive Lloyd of the West Indies has been appointed as the ICC Match Referee for the BCCI platinum jubilee one-day International between India and Pakistan, scheduled to be played at the Eden Gardens on November 13. 

Simon Taufel of Australia would be one of the two on-field umpires in the match. 

Meanwhile, former New Zealand captain Jeff Crowe has been nominated as the Match Referee for the two-Test series between India and South Africa next month. The Tests are to be held at Kanpur?s Green Park (Nov 20-24) and at the Eden Gardens (Nov 28-Dec 2). 

Australians Daryl Harper and Taufel would officiate as on-field umpires in this series. 

For India?s tour to Bangladesh in December, Englishman Chris Broad would be the Match Referee. Pakistan?s Aleem Dar and England?s Jeremy Lloyds would be the umpires for the first Test while another Englishman Mark Benson and Dar would do duty in the second Test. 

Dar would also officiate as the ICC-appointed umpire in the first and third ODI while Benson would do the job in the second ODI. (PTI) 

